This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing (NLP) and specifically on gender bias in NLP systems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses machine learning techniques and models, which suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a methodology for corpus augmentation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the impact of bias on society, which could potentially place it under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
